# Real-Time Chat Application

## Overview
This is a real-time chat application built with Node.js for the backend and React for the frontend. It utilizes Socket.io for real-time communication.

## Prerequisites
- Node.js (LTS version recommended)
- npm (Node package manager)

## Installation Guide

### Step 1: Clone the Repository
Clone the repository to your local machine using the following command:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/realtime-chat-app.git
cd realtime-chat-app

Step 2: Install Backend Dependencies
Navigate to the backend directory and install the required dependencies:
cd backend
npm install

Step 4: Start the Backend Server
Run the backend server using the following command
node server.js

Step 5: Install Frontend Dependencies
Open a new terminal window, navigate to the frontend directory, and install the required dependencies:
cd frontend
npm install


Step 6: Start the Frontend Application
Run the frontend application using the following commannd
npm start
This will start the React application, and it should open in your default web browser.

Usage
Open multiple browser windows or tabs to test the chat functionality.
Enter different usernames in each instance to simulate multiple users chatting in real-time.
Troubleshooting
If you encounter issues with untracked files or Git warnings, ensure that you are in the correct directory and that there are no nested Git repositories.
For line ending warnings, configure Git to handle line endings properly:
git config --global core.autocrlf true
